<button class="accordion">What is employee health and wellness?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Employee wellness programmes or wellness plans are a form of health benefit that many employers provide – in one way or another – in addition to health insurance. The definition of a wellness programme is a programme that helps employees stay healthy or – in some cases – helps them improve their health.</p></div>
<button class="accordion">How do employees get involved in health and wellness programmes at work?
</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Here are some ways to get staff members out of their comfort zone (and comfy chair) and on the road to health:</p>
<p></p><li>Walk the workplace wellness program talk</li>
<p></p><li>Look for help to broaden your workplace wellness programme</li>
<p></p><li>Wellness programme success may begin with small steps</li>
<p></p><li>Make your workplace wellness programme fun.</li>
/p></div>
<button class="accordion">What should a health and wellness programme include?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>An employer approach is to improve employee health, wellness programmes. It includes activities such as company-sponsored exercise, weight-loss competitions, educational seminars, tobacco-cessation programmes, and health screenings. These are designed to help employees eat better, lose weight, and improve overall physical health.</p></div>
<button class="accordion">Do health and wellness at work programmes reduce medical costs?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Workplace health and wellness at work programmes are one of the most effective and well-accepted cost reduction strategies. The government and universities have demonstrated that effective workplace health programmes don't eliminate the drivers of healthcare costs. Still, they do reduce the demand for healthcare services.</p></div>
<button class="accordion">Do you need a degree to become a health and wellness coach?</button>
